GOREVILLE GETS GRANT TO INSTALL NEW SAFETY DEVICES

With a grant from the state and help from local volunteers and the Goreville Police and Fire Department, Goreville Schools is installing new secondary safety barriers on all classroom doors this summer! The devices, recommended by the Illinois Terrorism Task Force School Safety Commission of which Goreville Superintendent Dr. Steve Webb is an appointed member, will secure the doors to prevent unauthorized entry in case of an intruder and/or other emergency lockdown. #BlackcatPride

ICYMI - The Goreville Schools Registration Day is tomorrow from 10 AM - 6 PM in the high school gym! Social distancing measures will be instituted so please follow the IDPH guidelines when you arrive. If you would rather not enter the building, you can download the registration materials from our website and drop them off in the box located outside of the high school doors and we can collect your fees later. Remember, parents will get to decide between in-person and remote learning this year but you DO NOT have to decide at registration. There are still several areas of guidance that are unclear at best, so please click the link below and fill out the survey by Sunday evening so that we have the most information possible to help guide our decisions on making the 2020-2021 school year the absolute best it can be! Thank you for your support! #BlackcatPride

post_text:
WELCOME BACK TO GOREVILLE SCHOOLS!

Goreville Schools will host our annual "Registration Day" next Thursday, July 16 from 10 AM - 6 PM in the high school gym (Pre-K will be in the Early Learning Center)! Of course, social distancing rules will apply and staff will monitor and limit the number of people in the facility at one time as IDPH has required. Registration forms can be downloaded from www.gorevilleschools.com. The school district has been meeting with our Return to School Planning Teams and are eager to get the school year started. Parents will be offered two choices for your children - in-person traditional school or remote learning. Parents do not have to make the choice now as we are in the very early stages of planning. While there are still many procedures to finalize in the near future, Goreville Schools is committed to returning to educating our children as normal and as safe as possible! As always, thank you for your support and GO BLACKCATS! #BlackcatPride

AreaSports.net
June 22 at 9:41 AM ¬∑

Since the State Tournament was canceled due to Covid, we will never know if the Goreville Blackcats would have won the Class 1A State Championship. They were in Peoria, ready to play when the decision to cancel went down. But what a year! The Blackcats had a record setting 35-2 season. Along the way they won the S-V Holiday Tournament, Black Diamond Conference West Title, 1A Regional, Sectional, and Super Sectional Champs. The IHSA gave them a Final Four Finalist Trophy. Here is a Team Photo to commemorate a storybook season for them. That's a LOT of hardware. Congratulations to Coach Todd Tripp and the players.

post_text: Class of 2020...WE ARE READY! Parking will be allowed at the Elementary School, Superintendent's Office, Baseball Field (South), and City Park with some parking along the road. We have designated handicap parking next to the high school parking lot (blue lines). We have portable restrooms available next to the Blackcats Marching Band trailer with plenty of hand sanitizer, but make sure you are socially distant when waiting in line. Also, make sure that your group of no more than 10 are socially distant to the other groups and follow all other Illinois Department of Public Health guidelines. WE LOVE THE #CLASSOF2020!

Also, make sure that your group of no more than 10 are socially distant to the other groups and follow all other Illinois Department of Public Health guidelines. WE LOVE THE #CLASSOF2020!

shared_text:
Monster Radio WGGH
April 24 at 2:41 PM ¬∑

Joins us tomorrow afternoon for a special broadcast. With the IHSA's cancelation of its spring state tournament series, the Goreville Lady Blackcats will not get a chance to defend their Class 1A State Softball championship from 2019. And while that means the Lady Blackcats are actually state champs for two years in a row, it's clearly not the same.

So in absence of high school sports, Saturday, Monster Radio WGGH will re-air last year's IHSA Class 1A state semifinal against Hardin Calhoun back-to-back with the state championship game against Illini Bluffs. The broadcast will begin at 1 p.m. We know this also isn't the same as playing this year, but we still hope you enjoy listening to an historic time in Goreville High School softball.

Joni Foster
April 1 at 6:51 PM ¬∑

These girls worked most of the day to get lunches ready for pick up and bus delivery for this Friday. Next week is spring break, so we decided to make more meals for the kids to have for the next week. We didn‚Äôt get everything done, but will be finished up by Friday! We are doing almost 1,000 meals a week when you take into account that each bag has 5 days worth of breakfast & lunch!! After spring break, we will be back at making meals for the Tuesday after spring breaküòä. Everyone on our list stays on the list, so no need to order a meal if you have already received some. If you have not received meals, you do need to let us know so we can have them ready. If your kids ride the bus, there is no need to call an order in, the buses will be stopping on their routes and honking so someone can come out and get them. Please keep in mind, pick up is Friday between 11-12, and no meals next week. Hope you are all doing well and staying safe!!‚ù§Ô∏è

Goreville School will be serving breakfast and lunch for this coming week. Last week we were only doing 12-15 daily. I know there are more families in need that may not have internet or Facebook, so please, anyone that has a neighbor with kids that might not know , ALL kids in Goreville School will get free meals while this shut down continues. This is breakfast AND lunch every day, we even load you up with extras to get through the weekend! We don‚Äôt want any child to go hungry and I feel like there are some that are,so please, talk to neighbors (6 feet apart tho), and let them know what we are doing. Tell them that some of our area businesses are also providing kids with a free meal, please help us get the word out! We are all in this together, and together, we WILL survive this. Please share!

post_text: Thank you SO MUCH to everyone who has volunteered to help and to the students, parents, and teachers for making our first E-Learning day a great experience! After further clarification from the state, all other days remaining in the mandated closure will be considered "Act of God" days meaning formal E-Learning with assessments is not allowed, but general instruction and electronic contact is and it is "encouraged" by the state. Therefore, our teachers have pledged to work with students throughout the closure, but it is not mandatory for all to participate. Also, the schools will not hold office hours due to the mandated social distancing. Meals will be served and we have had several volunteer to take the meals to you if you can not make it to the school. Please contact us if this is something you are interested in. You can always reach someone at contact@gorevilleschools.com or leave a phone message at the school. Again, thank you for your patience as we work through this! #BlackcatPride

GOREVILLE SCHOOLS PREPARE TO UTILIZE E-LEARNING DURING MANDATED SHUTDOWN

In preparation for the anticipated closure that was mandated today through March 30 by Governor Pritzker, Goreville Schools had been working toward a program to continue service to students so they do not lose progression. In order to limit contact, Goreville Schools will not be in session Monday, March 16 through Monday, March 30 and will resume March 31. The school will be sending an email to all parents and/or guardians regarding the logistics of the new E-Learning Program. Thank you for your support as we all work to make the best of a bad situation.

post_text: Due to the recommendations from the Peoria Public Health department to the HIS, tickets for this weekends IHSA State tournament have been limited. What this means is that all tickets that have been purchased for the tournament will not be honored. We are still unsure as to exactly what this means for parents, and are awaiting clarification from the IHSA this morning. Once we know, we will pass on the information immediately to the parents of our ballplayers. We are asking that the community please do not call the school. We will be getting information to you all by social media and email as soon as we get it. Every person that purchased a ticket will be getting a refund. This will begin next week. You will need to turn your ticket in to the hs office for a full refund. We are so very sorry and heartbroken for our kids and community, but the game will go on so in true Blackcat fashion‚Ä¶please send these kids your support and wish them the best of luck!!! Thank you for your patience and understanding. #BlackcatPride

post_text:
GOREVILLE SCHOOLS TO OFFER HAM RADIO TRAINING AND BECOMES EMERGENCY COMMUNICATIONS CENTER FOR JOHNSON COUNTY

Amateur Radio Station N9GHS (Goreville High School) is almost operational! We will offer Ham Radio courses to Goreville students as well as provide opportunities to talk to others across the world! We will also be conducting a class every month as well as a test session to get students, as well as the public licensed as Amateur Radio Operators! A special thanks ro Mike Hood and Dennis Brenningmeyer for setting up the system and the Southern Illinois Ham Radio Board for choosing us to provide this service in case of emergencies. More details will be forthcoming.

post_text: We have had an exciting and fun filled Homecoming week so far! Tomorrow is the final day of Spirit Week and it is SPIRIT DAY! All students in grades PK-12 are encouraged to show your Blackcat pride and dress in black and gold! There will be a pep rally at 10:00 a.m. and all students in the building will attend! The Homecoming game will be tomorrow night and the Blackcats will play Christopher. The freshman game will begin at 5:00 p.m. The Homecoming King and Queen coronation will be on Saturday and begin at 7:00 p.m. in the H.S. gym. Everyone is invited to attend the coronation. The dance will follow the coronation and is only for the high school students. We hope to see everyone decked out in their favorite black and gold spiritwear to show your support for the Blackcats!! #BlackcatPride

post_text: THE BLACKCATS ARE THE GOREVILLE INVITATIONAL TOURNAMENT CHAMPIONS! For the first time since 2012, the Blackcats have started the season 6-0 beating Harrisburg in a regular season game and now Johnston City, Hardin County, Hamilton County, Anna-Jonesboro and Benton for the G.I.T. Championship! Also, congratulations to Blackcats Landon Albright, Trent Glidewell, and Tournament MVP Nick Compton for being named All-Tournament! We are PROUD of you! #BlackcatPride
